Why?

780
00:34:14.853 --> 00:34:16.403
Are you using drugs?

781
00:34:16.438 --> 00:34:18.204
Are you getting drugs?
Mm-mm. No.

782
00:34:19.307 --> 00:34:20.940
Are you really sick?

783
00:34:22.026 --> 00:34:24.460
Yes. I am.

784
00:34:26.348 --> 00:34:30.050
Beth. I said it before.
and I really meant it:

785
00:34:30.085 --> 00:34:31.967
if I'm overstaying my welcome.

786
00:34:32.003 --> 00:34:33.502
I wish you would just say it.

787
00:34:34.856 --> 00:34:37.807
William. you are
overstaying your w...

788
00:34:37.842 --> 00:34:39.542
RANDALL:
Beth.

789
00:34:39.577 --> 00:34:41.161
What are you doing?

790
00:34:41.196 --> 00:34:43.158
Somebody has to ask
the questions here. baby...

791
00:34:43.182 --> 00:34:45.131
It's a cat.

792
00:34:46.651 --> 00:34:48.834
I have a cat.

793
00:34:48.870 --> 00:34:52.088
It's all I really have.

794
00:34:52.124 --> 00:34:54.774
His name's Clooney.

795
00:34:54.810 --> 00:34:59.162
One of those ironic names.
'cause he's a pretty ugly cat.

796
00:34:59.197 --> 00:35:01.764
I go back and forth to feed him.

797
00:35:01.800 --> 00:35:04.333
Three hours on the bus each day.

798
00:35:04.369 --> 00:35:07.103
Why wouldn't you just
tell us you had a cat?

799
00:35:07.139 --> 00:35:08.371
Nah.

800
00:35:08.407 --> 00:35:09.923
The little one has asthma

801
00:35:09.958 --> 00:35:11.336
and I knew if
I brought up the cat.

802
00:35:11.360 --> 00:35:12.469
you'd tell me to bring it.

803
00:35:12.493 --> 00:35:13.826
that would cause problems.

804
00:35:13.862 --> 00:35:15.556
And I don't want
to cause any problems.

805
00:35:15.580 --> 00:35:17.108
'cause if I cause problems.
I'd have to leave.

806
00:35:17.132 --> 00:35:18.331
And...

807
00:35:18.366 --> 00:35:21.150
and I don't want to leave.

808
00:35:21.185 --> 00:35:24.687
Six months ago. some doctor
told me I had three to live.

809
00:35:24.723 --> 00:35:27.857
But for some reason.
I don't feel so bad lately.

810
00:35:27.892 --> 00:35:30.326
Maybe to do with this house.

811
00:35:30.361 --> 00:35:32.991
I don't know.

812
00:35:33.015 --> 00:35:34.414
Truth is. I'd never thought

813
00:35:34.449 --> 00:35:36.043
I'd have anything
to care about again

814
00:35:36.067 --> 00:35:38.218
besides an ugly cat. so...

815
00:35:43.074 --> 00:35:45.375
Well. now I feel like a bitch.

816
00:35:45.410 --> 00:35:46.709
(Randall laughs)

817
00:35:46.744 --> 00:35:47.893
(William chuckles)

818
00:35:47.946 --> 00:35:48.995
It's not funny.

819
00:35:49.030 --> 00:35:50.163
It's not.

820
00:35:50.198 --> 00:35:52.398
(chuckling)
It's not funny.

821
00:35:57.439 --> 00:35:59.906
I'm about two hours away

822
00:35:59.941 --> 00:36:02.208
from throwing up violently.

823
00:36:02.244 --> 00:36:03.609
Mm.

824
00:36:03.644 --> 00:36:05.422
Are you gonna hold my hair
for me. Toby?

825
00:36:05.446 --> 00:36:07.547
Nope. I-I'm still gonna be
at this party.

826
00:36:07.582 --> 00:36:09.199
trying to bang a Gilmore Girl.

827
00:36:09.234 --> 00:36:10.983
(laughs)

828
00:36:11.018 --> 00:36:12.935
Well. go for both.

829
00:36:12.971 --> 00:36:15.305
Gil-more the Gil-merrier.

830
00:36:21.079 --> 00:36:24.797
It's always gonna be
about the weight for me. Toby.

831
00:36:26.301 --> 00:36:28.017
(sniffs)

832
00:36:28.053 --> 00:36:30.387
It's been my story ever since
I was a little girl.

833
00:36:33.241 --> 00:36:35.575
And every moment that
I'm not thinking about it.

834
00:36:35.610 --> 00:36:37.494
I'm thinking about it.

835
00:36:37.529 --> 00:36:39.245
Like...

836
00:36:39.281 --> 00:36:41.113
will this chair hold me?

837
00:36:41.166 --> 00:36:44.084
Will this dress fit me?

838
00:36:44.119 --> 00:36:47.269
And if I ever get pregnant.
would...

839
00:36:47.305 --> 00:36:49.472
will anyone ever notice?

840
00:36:54.479 --> 00:36:57.030
It's just at the core of
who I am. it's just deep inside.

841
00:36:57.065 --> 00:36:59.832
and eight tequila shots can only
mask that for a couple hours.

842
00:36:59.867 --> 00:37:01.907
So...
I know.

843
00:37:04.356 --> 00:37:05.571
And it was ten tequila shots.

844
00:37:05.607 --> 00:37:09.241
but I... I get it.
I know.

845
00:37:11.730 --> 00:37:13.329
And just for the record.

846
00:37:13.365 --> 00:37:18.384
um. this dress is fitting you
in all the right places.

847
00:37:18.419 --> 00:37:19.385
(purring)

848
00:37:19.421 --> 00:37:21.788
This old thing?
Uh-huh.

849
00:37:21.823 --> 00:37:23.072
I mean. I-I just threw it on.

850
00:37:23.107 --> 00:37:24.351
Oh. you just threw it on?
Mm-hmm.

851
00:37:24.375 --> 00:37:25.603
I didn't even think about it.

852
00:37:25.627 --> 00:37:28.394
(chuckles)

853
00:37:28.430 --> 00:37:29.812
(sighs)

854
00:37:31.883 --> 00:37:33.182
There he is.

855
00:37:35.804 --> 00:37:37.820
I told 'em to go
screw themselves.

856
00:37:37.856 --> 00:37:40.106
And what'd they say?

857
00:37:41.175 --> 00:37:43.442
A lot of mean. scary things.

858
00:37:48.183 --> 00:37:50.900
I'm gonna do theater.

859
00:37:50.935 --> 00:37:52.535
You know?

860
00:37:53.572 --> 00:37:55.855
I'm moving to New York.

861
00:38:00.344 --> 00:38:02.904
(whispering):
Show business.

862
00:38:12.540 --> 00:38:15.020
(sighs)
What are you doing out here?

863
00:38:18.179 --> 00:38:21.064
I don't like sleeping
far away from you.

864
00:38:23.885 --> 00:38:25.669
No more drinking.

865
00:38:25.704 --> 00:38:26.902
You can't just stop...

866
00:38:26.938 --> 00:38:28.170
I can.

867
00:38:28.206 --> 00:38:30.173
For you. I can.

868
00:38:31.643 --> 00:38:33.325
I will.

869
00:38:33.361 --> 00:38:35.595
(sighs)

870
00:38:37.798 --> 00:38:39.526
You know. when I was
a little boy.

871
00:38:39.550 --> 00:38:43.202
I didn't know what I wanted
to be when I grew up.

872
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:47.223
(inhales. exhales deeply)

873
00:38:47.258 --> 00:38:50.976
Adults always ask
little kids that.

874
00:38:53.348 --> 00:38:55.048
You know?

875
00:38:55.083 --> 00:38:57.666
I never had a good answer.

876
00:38:57.702 --> 00:39:00.369
Not until... not until I was 28.

877
00:39:01.957 --> 00:39:03.989
Till the day that I met you.

878
00:39:06.094 --> 00:39:08.945
That's when I knew exactly
what I wanted to be

879
00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:10.260
when I grew up.

880
00:39:12.266 --> 00:39:14.634
I wanted to be the man
that made you happy.

881
00:39:16.737 --> 00:39:19.071
(sighs)

882
00:39:19.107 --> 00:39:20.790
You make me happy.

883
00:39:20.825 --> 00:39:22.725
Not always.

884
00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:25.494
(scoffs)
Not lately.

885
00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:34.103
From here on out. I'm gonna be
an 11 for you. baby.

886
00:39:36.173 --> 00:39:38.607
No...

887
00:39:38.643 --> 00:39:41.239
Screw that.

888
00:39:41.263 --> 00:39:45.765
I'm gonna be a 12 for you.
from here out.

889
00:39:45.800 --> 00:39:49.102
I'll be an 11 for the kids.

890
00:39:49.137 --> 00:39:50.586
but you get a 12.

891
00:39:56.595 --> 00:39:58.477
Do you forgive me?

892
00:40:00.582 --> 00:40:04.150
You slept outside our bedroom
door like a Labrador.

893
00:40:06.521 --> 00:40:08.621
Of course I forgive you.

894
00:40:15.029 --> 00:40:16.762
Can I still give you my gift?

895
00:40:17.832 --> 00:40:19.815
If you insist.

896
00:40:29.694 --> 00:40:31.878
♪ Come down off your throne ♪

897
00:40:31.913 --> 00:40:33.529
Do you like it?

898
00:40:33.565 --> 00:40:35.281
♪ And leave your body alone ♪

899
00:40:35.317 --> 00:40:36.961
I got a moon because of...
Our song.

900
00:40:36.985 --> 00:40:38.518
Yeah.

901
00:40:38.553 --> 00:40:40.970
♪ Somebody must change ♪

902
00:40:41.006 --> 00:40:42.655
I'm never gonna take it off.

903
00:40:42.690 --> 00:40:44.223
♪ You are the reason ♪

904
00:40:44.258 --> 00:40:48.077
♪ I've been waiting so long ♪

905
00:40:48.112 --> 00:40:49.979
♪ Somebody holds the key ♪

906
00:40:50.014 --> 00:40:51.898
Do you like it?

907
00:40:51.933 --> 00:40:53.883
Does it look good?

908
00:40:53.918 --> 00:40:55.696
♪ But I'm near the end ♪
It's beautiful.

909
00:40:55.720 --> 00:40:57.053
Thank you.

910
00:40:57.088 --> 00:41:00.773
♪ I just ain't got the time ♪

911
00:41:00.808 --> 00:41:01.874
Mm.

912
00:41:01.909 --> 00:41:05.144
♪ And I'm wasted ♪

913
00:41:05.180 --> 00:41:07.091
♪ And I can't find my way home ♪
How much time we have
till the kids get up?

914
00:41:07.115 --> 00:41:09.515
I don't care about the kids.

915
00:41:12.370 --> 00:41:15.338
(moaning)
Pile drive!

916
00:41:15.373 --> 00:41:18.191
(yelling)
(laughing)

917
00:41:19.611 --> 00:41:24.430
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪

918
00:41:24.465 --> 00:41:26.565
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ♪

919
00:41:26.601 --> 00:41:30.436
♪ Ooh ooh-ooh ooh ♪

920
00:41:30.471 --> 00:41:33.973
♪ Come down on your own ♪

921
00:41:34.009 --> 00:41:37.409
♪ And leave your body alone ♪

922
00:41:37.445 --> 00:41:40.546
♪ Somebody must change ♪

923
00:41:40.581 --> 00:41:43.015
(laughing):
Daddy. stop! Daddy. stop!

924
00:41:43.051 --> 00:41:46.035
If you want to sleep in.
you have to pay the tickle tax!

925
00:41:46.071 --> 00:41:47.548
WILLIAM (laughing):
Tickle tax.

926
00:41:47.572 --> 00:41:49.066
(Randall sighs)

927
00:41:49.090 --> 00:41:50.734
(timer dings)
Oh. All right. come on. honey.

928
00:41:50.758 --> 00:41:51.724
It's time to take care of...

929
00:41:51.760 --> 00:41:52.854
WILLIAM:
Here you go.

930
00:41:52.878 --> 00:41:55.360
♪ But I'm near the end ♪

931
00:41:55.396 --> 00:41:56.557
(inhaler puffs)
WILLIAM:
Good.

932
00:41:56.581 --> 00:41:58.464
Big breath.

933
00:41:58.499 --> 00:42:00.227
Good.
(doorbell rings)

934
00:42:00.251 --> 00:42:02.034
You expecting somebody?

935
00:42:02.069 --> 00:42:04.620
♪ And I'm wasted ♪
No.

936
00:42:04.655 --> 00:42:07.073
♪ And I can't find my way home ♪

937
00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:09.108
TESS:
Grandma and Grandpa are here!

938
00:42:10.194 --> 00:42:12.361
I'll be in my room.

939
00:42:17.201 --> 00:42:22.588
♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪

940
00:42:22.624 --> 00:42:25.074
♪ But I can't find my way home ♪
Hey. Mom.

941
00:42:25.109 --> 00:42:26.709
Hey. Miguel.

942
00:42:26.744 --> 00:42:28.811
♪ But I can't find
my way home. ♪

943
00:42:28.847 --> 00:42:30.462
Hey.

